    <div id="fireModal" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close" onclick="closeModal('fire')">&times;</span>
            <h2>Functional Prototype of Modular IoT-Enabled Fire Protection Device</h2>
            
            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Final Project Result</h3>
                <div class="modal-main-image" id="fire-modal-image">
                    🔥 Upload your final project image to see it here
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="modal-links-section">
                <h4>📂 Complete Project Media & Documentation</h4>
                <div class="modal-links-grid">
                    <a href="#" class="modal-link-placeholder" id="fire-modal-gallery">
                        <span>📸</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Prototype Development Photos</strong><br>
                            <small>Click "Edit Links" in the project card to add Google Drive link</small>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                    <a href="#" class="modal-link-placeholder" id="fire-modal-video">
                        <span>🎥</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>System Demo & Testing Video</strong><br>
                            <small>Click "Edit Links" in the project card to add Google Drive link</small>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                    <a href="#" class="modal-link-placeholder" id="fire-modal-docs">
                        <span>🔧</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Technical Specifications</strong><br>
                            <small>Click "Edit Links" in the project card to add Google Drive link</small>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Project Overview</h3>
                <p>Developed a functional prototype of a modular, IoT-enabled fire protection device that integrates 
                real-time fire detection, directional water-based suppression, and remote alerting within a 
                self-contained unit. Designed specifically for infrastructure-limited, high-risk environments 
                such as large outdoor event spaces where traditional fire safety systems are inadequate.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Technical Architecture & Components</h3>
                <p><strong>Physical Structure:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cylindrical main structure (20" diameter, 60" height) with 360° access capability</li>
                    <li>Rectangular base (30" × 23" × 11") housing 50L integrated water storage</li>
                    <li>MS Steel construction (1.5-2mm thickness) with maintenance access doors</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Detection System:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>5 IR Flame Sensors providing 180° coverage with 80cm detection radius</li>
                    <li>Heat/flame detection with alert capabilities</li>
                    <li>Multi-sensor triangulation for fire location determination</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Suppression System:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Dual-action approach: Water spray + Fire extinguisher ball launcher</li>
                    <li>1HP Sharp Self-Priming Pump (3-4 kg/cm² pressure, 50 LPM flow)</li>
                    <li>Directional water nozzles with 25-30 feet spray distance</li>
                    <li>Air cannon system for fire extinguisher ball deployment</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>System Operation & Functionality</h3>
                <p><strong>Detection Phase:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Continuous environmental monitoring through strategic sensor placement</li>
                    <li>IR radiation threshold detection with verification protocols</li>
                    <li>False alarm prevention through multi-sensor verification</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Alert & Targeting Phase:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>LED status indicators (Green→Yellow→Red progression)</li>
                    <li>Audible buzzer activation for occupant notification</li>
                    <li>GSM module sends SMS alerts with location and timestamp</li>
                    <li>Automatic platform positioning toward detected fire direction</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Suppression Phase:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Coordinated platform rotation and nozzle elevation for optimal targeting</li>
                    <li>Water pump activation through SSR relay control</li>
                    <li>Regulated water flow with servo-controlled valve system</li>
                    <li>Continuous operation until manual reset or water depletion</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Industry Collaboration</h3>
                <p><strong>Industry Partner:</strong> Vision Safety India (Verna, Goa)</p>
                <p><strong>About Vision Safety India:</strong> Professional safety equipment supplier specializing 
                in Marine Safety, Industrial Safety, Fire Safety Consultancy, and Workplace Breathing Air Solutions.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Project Investment:</strong> ₹15,670 total cost</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Structural & Mechanical Materials: ₹5,782</li>
